TL;DR - Unique art and setting is marred by frustrating pace and timing, game is made longer unnecessarily. The art and atmosphere of the game as a whole is unique, well-crafted, and perfectly unsettling for the theme, but the game is unforgivably TEDIOUS. The game is already short and not very difficult, but only made longer by slow movement (one part played for laughs but comes across as annoying,) meticulous timing based puzzles, and unnecessary extra steps. I'm glad I got it on sale.

to display ads, which many anti-malware classes as a danger level of 
"HIGH". Full disclosure: I have not opened the app or played the game so I 
can't comment on the gameplay itself, but I don't think this kind of 
malware should be acceptable in a paid app and should not be supported 
(hence the one star rating). If the malware is removed I'd be happy to open 
the app, play the game and adjust my rating. Please support developers who 
value your data and privacy security.
